node.text:
Congrats @stephs_bilingual_scholars !! GIVEAWAY CLOSED! Happy back to school season! 🍎 Educators are working harder than ever, so we want to help in gifting a prize for the new school year! It’s super quick to enter to win a brand new MACBOOK PRO laptop:

1️⃣ Like this post and comment below: What is one goal you have for this school year? (and if it’s just to survive, we’re with you)! 😉❤️
2️⃣ Go to @luckyteachersgiveaway and follow the easy instructions on the post.
And that’s all! You’re entered! ✔️

Last day for entries is 8/22. Winner will be contacted on 8/23 in a group DM with a few of the hosting accounts, and must claim prize within 24 hours. WE WILL NEVER ASK YOU FOR CREDIT CARD INFORMATION (if a copycat account asks you for it, it’s a scam)! This is not in association with Instagram and is hosted by the participating accounts. Open Worldwide (a winner outside the U.S. will be awarded prize as a gift card).

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amber on August 18, 2021. May be an image of table and indoor.

node.text: After 18 months I finally got to teach kids in person today! My feet are swollen, and I’m exhausted, but I’m looking forward to an awesome school year with some awesome kids! ☺️🍎 #kindergarten

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amber on August 13, 2021. May be a cartoon of 4 people, child and text that says 'FIRST DAY OF KINDERGARTEN August 18, 2021 Mrs. Masters Class Mrs. Masters Class August 19, 2021 PKTEN'.

node.text: 🎉Our First Day of School is next Wednesday and I finally get to teach kids in person! 🙌🏻 It has been since March of 2020 🤯! We do a staggered start with our kindergarteners on Wednesday and Thursday with about half of the classes, and then they all come on Friday! I love taking pictures of them on their very first day! When is your first day of school?!

node.text: Hello, Third Trimester! 28 weeks 🙂Baby Masters is growing and moving around so much! I’m feeling great, but sleeping terribly! If you have any 😴recommendations, please put them in the comments! School starts next week so I need to figure this out! 🙃

node.text: A student gave this to me the week before schools shut down last March. We had no idea what was coming. I haven’t taught students in person since then. I’m posting again because I need all the motivation to finish this school year teaching online. I really miss teaching kids in person. That’s all.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amber on February 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
⬇️ Easy Math Game Idea

 -students spread out their pattern blocks and the teacher does the same
-teacher describes a shape or shapes (ex. Find a shape with four sides, or find the blue rhombus, or hold up shapes that make 7 sides all together) 
- students / teacher hold up the shape or shapes that were described. 
- if a student holds it up first, the class gets a point / if I hold it up first, the teacher gets a point. 

My students have loved playing this game. I like that it keeps them engaged, and that I get some valuable info about what my students know. Also, you should know that you’re playing against the entire class. The first time we played, I took it pretty easy on them and slowly grabbed the shapes. The next time, they actually beat me! They were so fast! 🤣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amber on February 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ice Breaker How Mabel Fairbanks Changed Figure Skating Rose Viña illustrated by Claire Almon'.

node.text: ⛸ Ice Breaker is definitely a book you’ll want to share with your students. Ice Breaker tells the story of Mabel Fairbanks who broke down color barriers in figure skating. Despite Mabel’s talent and hard work, she was still denied the opportunity to compete for an Olympic gold medal because of the color of her skin. Mabel became a coach, mentor, and advocate for equality in skating. She was the first Black women to be inducted into the U.S. Figure Skating Hall of Fame.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amber on February 14, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, child, people standing, tree and grass.

node.text: Grateful for this guy today, and every day! 💗 We “celebrated” with Chuy’s last night 🌮 and 🍕 for lunch today. We might go crazy and get 🍦 tonight. I mean Valentine’s Day is about the food right?!

💗❤️ so many possibilities! We explored this math problem in one of our live Meets today. Students worked independently and shared out at the end. We’ve been working hard to challenge our brains 🧠 and solve these types of problems in multiple ways. Some students were working on counting one to one, others were working on persevering and working the entire time, and others were working on writing number sentences.
